; Derived TP73 DeltaEx2,3 transcript sequences for RNA-read review.
; Created on 2026-05-02 from the local RefSeq/NCBI GenBank TP73 locus fixture
; test_files/tp73.ncbi.gb (GRCh38.p14 NC_000001.11:3652516..3736201).
;
; These records are not external accessions. They model the reported
; D_{Ex2,3}Np73 splice form by joining the full-length TAp73 5' exon directly
; to the fourth transcript exon, skipping the second and third transcript
; exons of the selected full-length source isoform.
;
; Alpha source: NM_005427.4 / RefSeq transcript variant 1.
;   Retained genomic ranges:
;   1..126;55034..55276;69506..69692;70839..70954;74600..74709;
;   75113..75255;75614..75702;76812..76933;77485..77633;78412..78550;
;   78948..79041;80232..83686
;   Derived CDS annotation below uses the downstream p73-frame ORF starting
;   at cDNA position 154 because the source TAp73 start codon lies in the
;   skipped exon-2/3 region.
;
; Beta source: NM_001204184.2 / RefSeq transcript variant 8.
;   Retained genomic ranges:
;   1..126;55034..55276;69506..69692;70839..70954;74600..74709;
;   75113..75255;75614..75702;76812..76933;77485..77633;78412..78550;
;   80232..83686
;   The source transcript carries the beta-like 3' coding terminus in the
;   local RefSeq record; derived CDS annotation again starts at cDNA position
;   154 after exon-2/3 skipping.
;
; Use as an extra transcript FASTA with RNA-read commands that accept repeated
; --transcript-fasta inputs. The matching curation/evaluation sidecar lives in
; assets/panels/tp73_delta_ex2_3_isoforms_v1.json.
;
